30 || II./JG 11 \u2013 Marx || Maj Anton Mader || [? /MI8]: 4000m || B-17 || C.2031/II ANr.16\n|-\n| 20 || 13 Nov '43 || 11:20 || II./JG 11 \u2013 V\u00f6rden || Obstlt Hermann Graf || F\u00fcrstenau [05Ost N/FQ73]: 8500m || P-38 || C.2031/II ANr.17\n|-\n| 21 || 26 Nov '43 || 12:30 || II./JG 11 \u2013 Plantl\u00fcnne || Obstlt Hermann Graf || near Bremen [05Ost N/ER27]: 7000m || B-17 || C.2031/II\n|-\n| 22 || 29 Nov '43 || 15:30 || II./JG 11 \u2013 Plantl\u00fcnne || Obstlt Hermann Graf || near Bremen [05Ost N/EQ57]: 8800m || P-47 || C.2031/II\n|-\n| 23 || 20 Dec '43 || 11:50 || II./JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || Obstlt Hermann Graf || Bremen: 9000m || P-51 || C.2031/II ANr.19; of USAAF 354 FG\n|-\n| 24 || 22 Dec '43 || ? || II./JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || Obstlt Hermann Graf || M\u00fcnster  || P-47 || Prien JG 1 & 11 lists\n|-\n| 25 || 5 January 1944 || ? || II./JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || Obstlt Hermann Graf || Kiel/Cuxhaven  || P-38 || Prien JG 1 & 11 lists\n|-\n| 26 || 30 Jan '44 || ? || II./JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || Obstlt Hermann Graf || [05Ost S/ ?]  || P-47 || Prien JG 1 & 11 lists\n|-\n| 27 || 11 Feb '44 || 12:15 || II./JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || Obstlt Hermann Graf || near St Wendel [05Ost S/SP6]: 8000m  || P-51 || C.2025/I ANr.20; 2nd Lt R. McDonald of 354 FG\n|-\n| 28 || 21 Feb '44 || 13:54 || II./JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || Obstlt Hermann Graf || NE of Minden: 8000m  || P-47 || C.2025/I ANr.14\n|-\n| 29 || 22 Feb '44 || 13:35 || II./JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || Obstlt Hermann Graf || near Blomberg: 2000m  || P-51 || C.2025/I ANr.15\n|-\n| 30 || 22 Feb '44 || 13:42 || II./JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || Obstlt Hermann Graf || near Detmold: 7100m  || B-17 || C.2025/I ANr.21\n|-\n| 31 || 11 Sep '44 || ? || Stab/JG 11 \u2013 Finsterwalde || - || ? : 150m  || P-51 || C.2027/II\n|-\n| 32 || 26 Sep '44 || 14:04 || Stab/JG 11 \u2013 G\u00fctersloh || - || Deventer [05Ost S/HN-GN]: 2000m || Typhoon || C.2027/II\n|-\n| 33 || 26 Sep '44 || 14:06 || Stab/JG 11 \u2013 G\u00fctersloh || - || Deventer [05Ost S/HN-GN]: 2000m || Typhoon || C.2027/II\n|-\n| 34 || 5 Dec '44 || 12:35 || Stab/JG 11 \u2013 Wunstorf || - || S of Mitteland Canal [05Ost S/GT]: 2-400m || P-51 || C.2027/II\n|-\n| MIA || 1 January 1945 || ? || Stab/JG 11 \u2013 Biblis || - || Asch, Belgium ||  || \n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Organization of the Luftwaffe (1933\u20131945)|Organizational Hierarchy of the Luftwaffe during WW II]]\n\n==Notes==\n\n===Footnotes===\n* {{note label|Note1|a|a}} Zorner (not being there) did not know the reason for putting on the uniform. But he speculated that Specht may have known about his impending death.\n* {{note label|Note1|b|b}} The similar but differing meaning of ''Oberleutnant'' and ''Oberstleutnant'' may have contributed to the misunderstanding. It is not clear whether Johnson himself said Specht's name was on the ID card. Johnson died in 1976 and the authors were unable to confirm this.<ref name=\"Johnmanrho.04.148\"/>\n* {{note label|Note3|c|c}} According to Uffz. Ludwig Bertram of I./JG 1, the ''Geschwader'' took off at 08:08 am.<ref>Manrho and P\u00fctz 2004, p. 167. (citation 19)</ref>\n\n===Citations===\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==References==\n{{Refbegin}}\n* Barbas, Bernd (1985). \t''Planes of the Luftwaffe Fighter Aces Vol I''. \tKookaburra Technical Publishing. \t{{ISBN|0-85880-048-9}}  includes a profile of his aircraft, p.&nbsp;168\n* {{Cite book| last=Caldwell |first=Donald |author2=Muller, Richard  | year=2007 | title=The Luftwaffe Over Germany: Defense of the Reich | publisher=MBI Publishing Company |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZDLNaRbHD7gC |isbn=978-1-85367-712-0|pages=|ref=}}\n* {{Cite book| last=Fellgiebel| first=Walther-Peer | year=1986 | title=Die Tr\u00e4ger des Ritterkreuzes des Eisernen Kreuzes 1939\u20131945 | publisher=Podzun-Pallas |url=|isbn=978-3-7909-0284-6|pages=|ref=}}\n* Forsythe, Robert (2011).    ''Luftwaffe Viermot Aces 1942-45''.\tOxford: Osprey Publishing Ltd.\t{{ISBN|1-84908-438-6}}.\n* {{Cite book| last=Franks 