e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u044b \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |language=ru |trans-title=Transportation volumes at Russian airports |publisher=[[Federal Air Transport Agency]] |website=www.favt.ru |access-date=23 October 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Murmansk Airport''' ({{lang-ru|\u0410\u044d\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0301\u0440\u0442 \u041c\u0443\u0301\u0440\u043c\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a}} or {{lang|ru|\u0410\u044d\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442 \u041c\u0443\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0448\u0438}}; {{Airport codes|MMK|ULMM|p=n}}) is an [[international airport]] serving the city [[Murmansk]] in [[Russia]]. It is located near the town of [[Murmashi]] in Murmansk's southern suburbs, {{convert|24|km|mi}} outside the city centre. It serves as the [[airline hub]] for [[Aeroflot-Nord]].\n\nAs of 2019, it is the [[List of the busiest airports in Russia|31st busiest airport in Russia]] and [[List of the busiest airports in the former USSR|53st busiest airport in the former USSR]]. The airport served 763,668 passengers in 2016, an increase of 1.65% from 2015. In 2017 it served 845,928 passengers, an increase of 10.8% from 2016.<ref>{{cite report|url=http://www.favt.ru/public/materials//c/9/0/b/2/c90b20ba7df9bbbed27c4ebfc6c5afac.pdf|publisher=[[Federal Air Transport Agency]]|title=\u041e\u0431\u044a\u0435\u043c\u044b \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0437\u043e\u043a \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0430\u044d\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u044b \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u044f\u043d\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044c-\u0434\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0431\u0440\u044c 2015-2016 \u0433\u0433|trans-title=Traffic volume at Russian airports in January\u2013December 2015-2016|page=3|location=Moscow|format=PDF|language=Russian|accessdate=26 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nPreviously, the airfield had military significance and was called Murmashi airfield. During The [[Soviet-Finnish war]], the 147th fighter aviation regiment was based at the airfield on I-15 bis, I-16 and I-153 aircraft. With the beginning of the great Patriotic war, the 147th fighter aviation regiment, based at the airfield, performed tasks to cover Murmansk and the Kirov railway from German air raids. From July 1941, the regiment received MiG-3 aircraft, which it used until the spring of 1942. In mid-July 1941, the regiment included four MiG-3s designed to intercept enemy bombers and by the end of the month received 17 MiG-3s. In January 1942, the regiment received P-40 Tomahawk aircraft.\n\nFor exemplary performance of command assignments at the front against the German invaders and displaying valor and courage, by the decree of the [[Presidium of the USSR Supreme Soviet]] from 22 February 1943, the regiment was awarded order of the red banner. The regiment was based at the airfield until the spring of 1945.\n\nIn November 2015, [[Novaport]] bought out the Murmansk Airport from its former owner, [[Gazprom]] Oil, with the aim to develop flights from the low-cost airline [[Pobeda (airline)|Pobeda]] to the airport.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rusaviainsider.com/novaport-intends-to-take-full-control-of-murmansk-airport/|title=Novaport intends to take full control of Murmansk Airport|website=Rusaviainsider.com|date=20 November 2015|access-date=9 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Terminals==\n\n===Passanger terminal===\n\nOn the ground floor of the only passenger terminal there are check-in counters, waiting room, international zone, cafes and souvenir shops. On the second floor there is a cafe, a Duty-free shop, airline representative offices and souvenir shops. The Duty-free store is located only in the international zone. The arrival zones are located on the first floors \u2014 in the right (\"arrival hall B\") and left (\"arrival hall A\") wings of the building. There is also a hall for VIP guests, where inspection and check-in takes place separately from other passengers.\n\n===Cargo terminal===\n\nThe cargo terminal with an area of 400\u043c\u00b2 is located on a fenced territory, in the area under responsibility for transport security.\n\n==Airlines and destinations==\n\n{{airport-dest-list\n|[[Aeroflot]]| [[Moscow\u2013Sheremetyevo]]<ref>{{cite news|last=L|first=J|title=AEROFLOT Plans Moscow \u2013 Arkhangelsk / Murmansk Service from Jan 2015|url=http://airlineroute.net/2014/04/24/su-arhmmk-jan15/|accessdate=24 April 2014|newspaper=Airline Route|date=24 April 2014}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Azur Air]] | '''Seasonal charter:''' [[Antalya Airport|Antalya]] (resumes {{date|2020-4-25}})<ref name=\"MMK_S20_Charters\" />\n<!-- -->\n| [[Finnair]] | '''Seasonal charter:''' [[Vantaa Airport|Helsinki]] (resumes {{date|2020-5-9}})<ref name=\"MMK_S20_Charters\">{{cite news |title=\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0447\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0435\u0440 \u0438\u0437 \u041c\u0443\u0440\u043c\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0432 \u0410\u043d\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u044e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0442 \u0432 \u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u043b\u0435 |url=https://b-port.com/news/236305 |accessdate=6 February 2020 |work=\u0418\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u00ab\u0411\u0438-\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u00bb |date=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Nordwind Airlines]] | '''Seasonal charter:''' [[Antalya Airport|Antalya]] (resumes {{date|2020-4-27}})<ref name=\"MMK_S20_Charters\" />\n<!-- -->\n| [[Pobeda (airline)|Pobeda]]| [[Moscow\u2013Vnukovo]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=\u041f\u043b\u043e\u0445\u043e\u0442\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e |first1=\u042e\u0440\u0438\u0439 |title=\"\u041f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0430\" \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442 \u043b\u0435\u0442\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0438\u0437 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b \u0432 \u041c\u0443\u0440\u043c\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a |url=http://www.travel.ru/news/2019/07/26/262389.html |accessdate=31 July 2019 |work=Travel.ru |date=31 July 2019 |language=ru}}</ref><ref>{